---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Roadmap"
  description="A focused roadmap for CodeArmy: current priorities, next steps, and explicit non-goals."
>
  <section class="container page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Roadmap</p>
    <h1>Ship a focused product before a broad platform.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      CodeArmy is being built in stages. Each version has a clear boundary: what we are
      committing to now, what comes next, and what we are explicitly not doing yet.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container page-body">
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>v0.1 — Now</h3>
        <p class="text-secondary">Focused front door</p>
        <ul class="page-list">
          <li>Landing page that explains the product in 10 seconds</li>
          <li>Docs entry and practical Quickstart</li>
          <li>Clear narrative: repo-first campaigns, not generic agents</li>
          <li>Research credibility (real use cases mentioned)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-secondary" style="margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.875rem;">
          <strong>Why first:</strong> Without a credible front door, nothing else matters.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>v0.2 — Next</h3>
        <p class="text-secondary">Runnable workflow</p>
        <ul class="page-list">
          <li>CLI for campaign create/reconcile/report</li>
          <li>MCP server for Trae Solo integration</li>
          <li>Starter Skills pack</li>
          <li>Case studies from real research workflows</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-secondary" style="margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.875rem;">
          <strong>Why second:</strong> Make the narrative executable before adding breadth.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>v0.3 — Later</h3>
        <p class="text-secondary">Team scale</p>
        <ul class="page-list">
          <li>Feishu sync for approvals and reports</li>
          <li>Multi-member campaign visibility</li>
          <li>Extended examples and templates</li>
          <li>Optional self-hosted routing</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-secondary" style="margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.875rem;">
          <strong>Why third:</strong> Team features only after solo workflow is solid.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container page-body">
    <div class="callout" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);">
      <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Explicit Non-Goals</h3>
      <p>These are intentionally out of scope for the current phase:</p>
      <ul class="page-list">
        <li><strong>Generic chatbot:</strong> CodeArmy is not competing with conversational AI interfaces.</li>
        <li><strong>Heavy web infrastructure:</strong> No backends, databases, or dynamic forms in v1.</li>
        <li><strong>App-like complexity:</strong> The site stays static and GitHub Pages-friendly.</li>
        <li><strong>Platform promises before product:</strong> We will not publish feature matrices with dates we cannot commit to.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container page-body">
    <div class="split-grid">
      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Current focus</strong>
        <p style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0;">
          v0.1 is the only commitment right now. Everything else is directional, not promised.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; justify-content: flex-end;">
        <a class="button" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}docs/quickstart/`}>Read Quickstart</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Back to Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
